Metrics are used to measure:

"How well the model is performing."

Different problems use different metrics.

=====================

| Metric Type           | Used For                 | Example    |
| --------------------- | ------------------------ | ---------- |
| Accuracy Metrics      | Classification           | Accuracy   |
| Probabilistic Metrics | Probability prediction   | Log Loss   |
| Regression Metrics    | Number prediction        | MSE        |
| TP/TN Metrics         | Important classification | Precision  |
| Segmentation Metrics  | Pixel prediction         | IoU        |
| Hinge Metrics         | SVM                      | Hinge Loss |


==========================


1️⃣ Accuracy Metrics

Used for:

Classification problems

Checks:

How many predictions are correct.

Accuracy Formula

Accuracy=

(Correct Predictions/Total Predictions) x 100

Example

| Total Images | Correct Predictions |
| ------------ | ------------------- |
| 100          | 92                  |

Accuracy = 92%

========================================

Real-time Example

Like:

Exam score percentage.

=======================================

2️⃣ Probabilistic Metrics

Used when:

Model predicts probabilities

Measures:

Confidence quality of predictions
Common Metrics
Cross Entropy
Log Loss
Example

Prediction:

Cat = 0.95
Dog = 0.05

Good probability prediction → low loss

Real-time Example

Like:

Weather app saying:
"95% chance of rain"

===========================

3️⃣ Regression Metrics

Used for:

Continuous number prediction

Examples:

House price prediction
Temperature prediction


Common Regression Metrics
-------------------------

| Metric | Meaning                 |
| ------ | ----------------------- |
| MAE    | Mean Absolute Error     |
| MSE    | Mean Squared Error      |
| RMSE   | Root Mean Squared Error |


======================

Example
Actual Price = ₹10 lakh
Predicted = ₹9 lakh

Error = ₹1 lakh

MSE Formula

MSE=n1​∑i=1n​(yi​−y^​i​)2

Real-time Example

Like:

Difference between estimated bill and actual bill.

======================

4️⃣ Classification Metrics Based on True/False Positives & Negatives

Used when:

Accuracy alone is not enough

Important in:

Medical diagnosis
Fraud detection
Spam filtering

Four Important Terms
-------------------

| Term                | Meaning                 |
| ------------------- | ----------------------- |
| True Positive (TP)  | Correctly predicted YES |
| True Negative (TN)  | Correctly predicted NO  |
| False Positive (FP) | Wrong YES prediction    |
| False Negative (FN) | Wrong NO prediction     |


============================

Common Metrics

| Metric    | Purpose                       |
| --------- | ----------------------------- |
| Precision | Correct positive predictions  |
| Recall    | Finding all positives         |
| F1 Score  | Balance of precision & recall |

============================

Precision Formula

Precision=

TP / TP+FP
	​
-----------------

Recall Formula

Recall=

TP / TP+FN

=================

Real-time Example
Spam Detection
FP → Important email becomes spam
FN → Spam enters inbox

============================

5️⃣ Image Segmentation Metrics

Used in:

Object boundary detection
Medical imaging
Self-driving cars

Model predicts:

Pixel-by-pixel classification

Common Metrics
---------------

| Metric           | Meaning                 |
| ---------------- | ----------------------- |
| IoU              | Intersection over Union |
| Dice Coefficient | Similarity score        |


=======================

IoU Formula

IoU = \frac{\text{Intersection}}{\text{Union}

Real-time Example

Like:

Comparing actual object outline vs predicted outline.

==============

6️⃣ Hinge Metrics (Maximum-Margin Classification)

Used mainly in:

Support Vector Machines (SVM)

Goal:

Create maximum distance between classes.

Hinge Loss Formula

Hinge Loss=max(0,1−y⋅f(x))

Real-time Example

Like:

Keeping two teams separated with large gap.

